Your personal data is 100% encrypted and protected. We never store (or have access to) your bank login details. If you want to know all the cool ways we do that you can take a look here https:// help.withplum.com/hc/en-us/artic les/115000670885-Is-my-data-safe- …

At the moment this means users connect Plum to their bank account in two ways - (i) read-only access to your bank account, which we use to determine auto-savings and insights (ii) a Direct Debit Mandate (like your phone company), which is used for the auto-savings.

This in mind, Plum auto-savings aim to help people overcome this problem, and then our investment product strives to give people realistic options where they can actually get returns on their hard-earned cash. Please do be aware capital invested is at risk!

The problem with savings accounts is two-fold: firstly, the interest accrued is lower than inflation in most cases (sigh); secondly, the struggle is doubled in that most people don't get to the point where they feel they can ever put their money to work (savings, or investments).

Our focus so far has been on creating a portfolio of options where the user can select their risk and get better prospective returns. We feel that providing customers with diverse investment options (and the power of compound interest!) should be made available to everybody.

Hi Emily FSCS was created to protect consumers against the risk posed by banks lending out their deposits. We actually don’t lend out money in Plum like banks do so we don’t make any interest on it at all. Savings with Plum are held as “e-money” and cannot be lent out by Barclays

However, if Barclays were to go under, your money may NOT be protected by the Financial Services Compensation Scheme, so you could lose your cash – you need to decide if you’re happy to take the risk. this is extremely concerning

We never tell Facebook (or anyone) any of your details or transactions. When you sign up, your account setup is done in a secure webview generated by our servers, not by FB. You do not even need a FB account to use Plum http:// blog.withplum.com/can-i-still-us e-plum-without-facebook/ …

We have also been recommended by reputable organisations such as @WhichUK and @MoneySavingExp who are extremely rigorous with their background checks and actively work to prevent scams. MSE article here: http://www. moneysavingexpert.com/team-blog/2017 /03/14/meet-new-facebook-friend-automatic-savings-app-lives-messenger/ …

Hey Emily, Completely understand. Plum works with regulated payments institutions and is itself registered with the FCA as an appointed representative for two of its partners. Plum is also in the final stages of FCA registration as an Account Information Service Provider.

Due to these contractual relationships we ensure your funds are safe and all financial elements of the products are regulated accordingly. Full details here: https:// help.withplum.com/hc/en-us/artic les/115000659609-How-is-Plum-regulated- …

To clarify again Plum is not a bank. We are a chatbot designed to help people save. As we don’t lend out money in Plum like banks do or make any interest on it. FSCS was created to protect consumers against the risk posed by banks lending out their deposits. :)

Hey Plumsters, anyone around on Monday the 8th for pizza and a chat? We are shooting our new user testimonial videos and we want you! Come to our London HQ for 20 mins and tell us what you think. You can book available slots here :) https:// calendly.com/plumvideo/20mi n/01-08-2018 …

No we are not directly regulated by the FCA. We run all these services by working together with regulated payments providers GoCardless for direct debits, and MangoPay when it comes to the holding of funds.

No customer protection is not the same as banks. Funds are not FSCS protected, but protected along client money regulations. Plum has publicly available financial statements through Companies House which are prepared by external accountants.
